[{"_1":2},"routes/puzzle-detail",{"_3":4},"data",{"_5":6,"_7":8,"_9":10},"status","success","slug","brothers-and-sisters-i-have-none","puzzle",{"_7":8,"_11":12,"_34":35,"_36":37,"_38":39,"_40":41},"metadata",{"_13":14,"_15":16,"_17":18,"_19":20,"_22":23,"_25":26,"_27":28,"_29":30,"_31":32,"_33":32},"id","puzzle-62","title","Brothers and Sisters I Have None","difficulty","easy","concepts",[21],"logic","tags",[24],"has-solution","credit","Classic riddle. Question and solution written by Puzzlestone Peak.","dateCreated","2026-02-04","lastUpdated","2026-02-05","preview","A man is looking at a photograph of someone. His friend asks who it is. The man replies, “Brothers and sisters, I have none. But that man’s father is my...","websitePreview","content","<p>A man is looking at a photograph of someone. His friend asks who it is.</p>\n<p>The man replies, “Brothers and sisters, I have none. But that man’s father is my father’s son.”</p>\n<p>Who is in the photograph?</p>\n<details class=\"content-block solution-block\" data-type=\"solution\"><summary class=\"solution-label\">Solution</summary><div class=\"solution-content markdown-content prose max-w-none px-4 py-4 space-y-4\"><p><strong>Answer</strong>: The photograph is of the man’s son.</p><p>Since the man has no brothers or sisters, “my father’s son” must refer to himself.</p><p>Thus, “that man’s father is my father’s son” means “that man’s father is me”.</p><p>The photograph is of his son.</p></div></details>","rawContent","\nA man is looking at a photograph of someone. His friend asks who it is.\n\nThe man replies, “Brothers and sisters, I have none. But that man’s father is my father’s son.”\n\nWho is in the photograph?\n\n:::solution\n**Answer**: The photograph is of the man’s son.\n\nSince the man has no brothers or sisters, “my father’s son” must refer to himself.\n\nThus, “that man’s father is my father’s son” means “that man’s father is me”.\n\nThe photograph is of his son.\n:::\n","dynamicBlocks",[],"inlineComponents",{}]
